      <akn:section eId="sec_16_2390">
        <akn:num>16-2390</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Jurisdiction.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_16-2390_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Subject to subsection (b) of this section, the court shall have jurisdiction to enter guardianship order and shall retain jurisdiction to enforce, modify, or terminate a guardianship order until a child reaches 21 years of age; provided, that when the child reaches 18 years of age, the child consents and the court finds it is in the best interest of the child.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_16-2390_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A child who exits foster care to guardianship may not reenter foster care after age 18.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
